g.text: 128th Brigade (1/4th, 2/4th and 5th Battalions) joined 46th (North Midland) Division in Kent.
2nd Battalion left Gourock, Scotland as part of the 1st Army to take part in the invasion of North Africa.
2nd Battalion in Battle of Tebourba; Maj HW Le Patourel awarded Victoria Cross.
128th Bde (1/4th, 2/4th & 5th Bns) embarked at Gourock as part of 46th Div to join the 1st Army in Tunisia.
128th Bde (1/4th, 2/4th & 5th Bns) disembarked at Bone, North Africa.

128th Bde (46th Div) in positions covering vital communication centres of Beja. 2nd/4th & 1st/4th Bns astride Hunts Gap, 5th Bn and 155 Bty RA in isolated positions at Sidi Nisr, 12 miles NE towards Mateur.
2nd Bn (re-formed after the battle of Tebourba) rushed South from Munchar to stop German attack through Kasserine Gap.
Battle of Sidi Nsir. Gallant delaying action by 5th Bn and 155 Bty, 172 Fd Regt RA overrun by enemy Armoured Force advancing on Beja.

Battle of Hunts Gap. 2/4th, 1/4th and remnants of 5th Bn (from Sidi Nisr) successfully held up strong enemy armoured and infantry attacks on Beja. In four days’ fighting, 2/4th Bn reduced to one company strength.
2nd Bn joined 128th Bde in Hunts Gap and with 1/4th Bn made several unsuccessful attempts to regain positions lost on 28th Feb.

128th Bde. 1/4th and 2/4th Bns, after long night advance, crossed River Marguellin and captured Pichon. The Bde then advanced 38 miles towards Kairouan after having spent the previous month in static waterlogged posns.
128th Bde rejoined 46th Div at El Aroussa to prepare for attack North of Bou Arada.
Battle of Bou Arada. Night attack by 128th Bde (1/4th, 2/4th and 5th Bns) under a heavy barrage on strongly prepared positions held by the Hermann Goering Division on Melhalla and Seba Argout.
2/4th Bn left 128 Bde at Tebourba for combined operations training at Bougie and was replaced by 2nd Bn.
128 Bde (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Bns) took part in the pursuit and final surrender of Von Arnem’s forces in Cap Bon area. End of North African Campaign.
2/4th Bn – combined operations training with 20 and 21 Beach Groups at Oued Marsa and Bougie in preparation for the invasion of Sicily.
128 Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions), Combined Operations training at Djidjelli in preparation for invasion of Italy.
